Constructor:
A constructor is a special method in a class that runs automatically when you create an object.
1. Its job? To initialize the object.
2. It has no return type (not even void)
3. It has the same name as the class

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Constructor:
1. A default constructor is a constructor that takes no arguments.
2. If no constructor is explicitly defined in a class, the Java compiler automatically provides a public, no-argument default constructor.
3. This automatically generated default constructor initializes instance variables to their default values (e.g., 0 for numeric types, false for booleans, null for object references).

import java.util.Scanner;

class Constuctor{
    String name;
    int roll;

    public void display(){
        System.out.println("Name: "+name+"\nRoll no.: "+roll);
    }
}

public class constructor {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in=new Scanner(System.in);

        Constuctor d=new Constuctor();
        d.display(); //null 0
        
        in.close();
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Parameterized Constructor:
1. A parameterized constructor is a constructor that accepts one or more arguments.
2. It allows for initializing object properties with specific values provided during object creation, rather than relying on default values.
3. If a parameterized constructor is defined in a class, the compiler will not automatically provide a default constructor. If a no-argument constructor is still desired, it must be explicitly defined.

import java.util.Scanner;

class Constuctor{
    String name;
    int roll;
    
    //default constructor
    Constuctor(){
        name="maha";
        roll=215;
    }

    //parameterised constructor
    Constuctor(String n,int r){
        name=n;
        roll=r;
    }
    public void display(){
        System.out.println("Name: "+name+"\nRoll no.: "+roll);
    }
}

public class constructor {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in=new Scanner(System.in);

        Constuctor d=new Constuctor();
        d.display(); //maha 215

        Constuctor p=new Constuctor(in.nextLine(),in.nextInt());
        p.display();

        in.close();
    }
}

